#. <section class="sutta" id="sn12.65"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn12.65:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 12"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 12"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.65:0.2"
msgid "7. Mahāvagga"
msgstr "7. The Great Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn12.65:0.3"
msgid "65. Nagarasutta"
msgstr "65. The City"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.65:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn12.65:1.2"
msgid ""
"“Pubbe me, bhikkhave, sambodhā anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva sato "
"etadahosi:"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, before my awakening—when I was still unawakened but intent on "
"awakening—I thought:"

msgctxt "sn12.65:1.3"
msgid ""
"‘kicchā vatāyaṃ loko āpanno jāyati ca jīyati ca mīyati ca cavati ca "
"upapajjati ca."
msgstr ""
"‘Alas, this world has fallen into trouble. It’s born, grows old, dies, "
"passes away, and is reborn,"

msgctxt "sn12.65:1.4"
msgid "Atha ca panimassa dukkhassa nissaraṇaṃ nappajānāti jarāmaraṇassa."
msgstr ""
"yet it doesn’t understand how to escape from this suffering, from old age "
"and death."

msgctxt "sn12.65:1.5"
msgid "Kudāssu nāma imassa dukkhassa nissaraṇaṃ paññāyissati jarāmaraṇassā’ti?"
msgstr ""
"Oh, when will an escape be found from this suffering, from old age and "
"death?’"

msgctxt "sn12.65:1.6"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to me:"

msgctxt "sn12.65:1.7"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho sati jarāmaraṇaṃ hoti, kiṃpaccayā jarāmaraṇan’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘When what exists is there old age and death? What is a condition for old "
"age and death?’"

msgctxt "sn12.65:1.8"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya abhisamayo:"
msgstr "Then, through proper attention, I comprehended with wisdom:"

msgctxt "sn12.65:1.9"
msgid "‘jātiyā kho sati jarāmaraṇaṃ hoti, jātipaccayā jarāmaraṇan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘When rebirth exists there’s old age and death. Rebirth is a condition for "
"old age and death.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.65:2.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to me:"

msgctxt "sn12.65:2.2"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho sati jāti hoti … pe …"
msgstr "‘When what exists is there rebirth? …"

msgctxt "sn12.65:2.3"
msgid "bhavo hoti …"
msgstr "continued existence …"

msgctxt "sn12.65:2.4"
msgid "upādānaṃ hoti …"
msgstr "grasping …"

msgctxt "sn12.65:2.5"
msgid "taṇhā hoti …"
msgstr "craving …"

msgctxt "sn12.65:2.6"
msgid "vedanā hoti …"
msgstr "feeling …"

msgctxt "sn12.65:2.7"
msgid "phasso hoti …"
msgstr "contact …"

msgctxt "sn12.65:2.8"
msgid "saḷāyatanaṃ hoti …"
msgstr "the six sense fields …"

msgctxt "sn12.65:2.9"
msgid "nāmarūpaṃ hoti …"
msgstr "name and form …"

msgctxt "sn12.65:2.10"
msgid "kiṃpaccayā nāmarūpan’ti?"
msgstr "What is a condition for name and form?’"

msgctxt "sn12.65:2.11"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya abhisamayo:"
msgstr "Then, through proper attention, I comprehended with wisdom:"

msgctxt "sn12.65:2.12"
msgid "‘viññāṇe kho sati nāmarūpaṃ hoti, viññāṇapaccayā nāmarūpan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘When consciousness exists there are name and form. Consciousness is a "
"condition for name and form.’"

msgctxt "sn12.65:2.13"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to me:"

msgctxt "sn12.65:2.14"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho sati viññāṇaṃ hoti, kiṃpaccayā viññāṇan’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘When what exists is there consciousness? What is a condition for "
"consciousness?’"

msgctxt "sn12.65:2.15"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya abhisamayo:"
msgstr "Then, through proper attention, I comprehended with wisdom:"

msgctxt "sn12.65:2.16"
msgid "‘nāmarūpe kho sati viññāṇaṃ hoti, nāmarūpapaccayā viññāṇan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘When name and form exist there’s consciousness. Name and form are a "
"condition for consciousness.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.105"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.65:3.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi—"
msgstr "Then it occurred to me:"

# SF 154 has an interesting variant: vijñānātpratyudāvartate mānasaṃ nātaḥ pareṇa vyativartate. see SN 22.90
msgctxt "sn12.65:3.2"
msgid "paccudāvattati kho idaṃ viññāṇaṃ nāmarūpamhā na paraṃ gacchati."
msgstr ""
"This consciousness turns back from name and form, and doesn’t go beyond that."

# BB’s rendering makes it seem that the mutual conditioning clauses are syntactically distinct, and connected to this sentence. This is the case in the related passage at DN 15. But here in the Pali this sentence serves to introduce the entire set of conditions.
msgctxt "sn12.65:3.3"
msgid ""
"Ettāvatā jāyetha vā jīyetha vā mīyetha vā cavetha vā upapajjetha vā, yadidaṃ "
"nāmarūpapaccayā viññāṇaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"This is the extent to which one may be reborn, grow old, die, pass away, or "
"reappear. That is: name and form are conditions for consciousness."

msgctxt "sn12.65:3.4"
msgid "viññāṇapaccayā nāmarūpaṃ;"
msgstr "Consciousness is a condition for name and form."

msgctxt "sn12.65:3.5"
msgid "nāmarūpapaccayā saḷāyatanaṃ;"
msgstr "Name and form are conditions for the six sense fields."

msgctxt "sn12.65:3.6"
msgid "saḷāyatanapaccayā phasso … pe …"
msgstr "The six sense fields are conditions for contact. …"

msgctxt "sn12.65:3.7"
msgid "evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa samudayo hoti."
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering originates."

msgctxt "sn12.65:3.8"
msgid ""
"‘Samudayo, samudayo’ti kho me, bhikkhave, pubbe ananussutesu dhammesu "
"cakkhuṃ udapādi ñāṇaṃ udapādi paññā udapādi vijjā udapādi āloko udapādi."
msgstr ""
"‘Origination, origination.’ Such was the vision, knowledge, wisdom, "
"realization, and light that arose in me regarding teachings not learned "
"before from another."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.65:4.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to me:"

msgctxt "sn12.65:4.2"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho asati, jarāmaraṇaṃ na hoti;"
msgstr "‘When what doesn’t exist is there no old age and death?"

msgctxt "sn12.65:4.3"
msgid "kissa nirodhā jarāmaraṇanirodho’ti?"
msgstr "When what ceases do old age and death cease?’"

msgctxt "sn12.65:4.4"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya abhisamayo:"
msgstr "Then, through proper attention, I comprehended with wisdom:"

msgctxt "sn12.65:4.5"
msgid "‘jātiyā kho asati, jarāmaraṇaṃ na hoti;"
msgstr "‘When rebirth doesn’t exist there is no old age and death."

msgctxt "sn12.65:4.6"
msgid "jātinirodhā jarāmaraṇanirodho’ti."
msgstr "When rebirth ceases old age and death cease.’"

msgctxt "sn12.65:4.7"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to me:"

msgctxt "sn12.65:4.8"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho asati jāti na hoti … pe …"
msgstr "‘When what doesn’t exist is there no rebirth …"

msgctxt "sn12.65:4.9"
msgid "bhavo na hoti …"
msgstr "continued existence …"

msgctxt "sn12.65:4.10"
msgid "upādānaṃ na hoti …"
msgstr "grasping …"

msgctxt "sn12.65:4.11"
msgid "taṇhā na hoti …"
msgstr "craving …"

msgctxt "sn12.65:4.12"
msgid "vedanā na hoti …"
msgstr "feeling …"

msgctxt "sn12.65:4.13"
msgid "phasso na hoti …"
msgstr "contact …"

msgctxt "sn12.65:4.14"
msgid "saḷāyatanaṃ na hoti …"
msgstr "six sense fields …"

msgctxt "sn12.65:4.15"
msgid "nāmarūpaṃ na hoti."
msgstr "name and form?"

msgctxt "sn12.65:4.16"
msgid "Kissa nirodhā nāmarūpanirodho’ti?"
msgstr "When what ceases do name and form cease?’"

msgctxt "sn12.65:4.17"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya abhisamayo:"
msgstr "Then, through proper attention, I comprehended with wisdom:"

msgctxt "sn12.65:4.18"
msgid "‘viññāṇe kho asati, nāmarūpaṃ na hoti;"
msgstr "‘When consciousness doesn’t exist name and form don’t come to be."

msgctxt "sn12.65:4.19"
msgid "viññāṇanirodhā nāmarūpanirodho’ti."
msgstr "When consciousness ceases name and form cease.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.65:5.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to me:"

msgctxt "sn12.65:5.2"
msgid "‘kimhi nu kho asati viññāṇaṃ na hoti;"
msgstr "‘When what doesn’t exist is there no consciousness?"

msgctxt "sn12.65:5.3"
msgid "kissa nirodhā viññāṇanirodho’ti?"
msgstr "When what ceases does consciousness cease?’"

msgctxt "sn12.65:5.4"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, yoniso manasikārā ahu paññāya abhisamayo:"
msgstr "Then, through proper attention, I comprehended with wisdom:"

msgctxt "sn12.65:5.5"
msgid "‘nāmarūpe kho asati, viññāṇaṃ na hoti;"
msgstr "‘When name and form don’t exist, there is no consciousness."

msgctxt "sn12.65:5.6"
msgid "nāmarūpanirodhā viññāṇanirodho’ti."
msgstr "When name and form cease, consciousness ceases.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.65:6.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi—"
msgstr "Then it occurred to me:"

msgctxt "sn12.65:6.2"
msgid "adhigato kho myāyaṃ maggo bodhāya yadidaṃ—"
msgstr "I have discovered the path to awakening. That is:"

msgctxt "sn12.65:6.3"
msgid "nāmarūpanirodhā viññāṇanirodho;"
msgstr "When name and form cease, consciousness ceases."

msgctxt "sn12.65:6.4"
msgid "viññāṇanirodhā nāmarūpanirodho;"
msgstr "When consciousness ceases, name and form cease."

msgctxt "sn12.65:6.5"
msgid "nāmarūpanirodhā saḷāyatananirodho;"
msgstr "When name and form cease, the six sense fields cease."

msgctxt "sn12.65:6.6"
msgid "saḷāyatananirodhā phassanirodho … pe …"
msgstr "When the six sense fields cease, contact ceases. …"

msgctxt "sn12.65:6.7"
msgid "evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa nirodho hoti."
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering ceases."

msgctxt "sn12.65:6.8"
msgid ""
"‘Nirodho, nirodho’ti kho me, bhikkhave, pubbe ananussutesu dhammesu cakkhuṃ "
"udapādi ñāṇaṃ udapādi paññā udapādi vijjā udapādi āloko udapādi."
msgstr ""
"‘Cessation, cessation.’ Such was the vision, knowledge, wisdom, realization, "
"and light that arose in me regarding teachings not learned before from "
"another."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.106"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.65:7.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso araññe pavane caramāno passeyya purāṇaṃ maggaṃ "
"purāṇañjasaṃ pubbakehi manussehi anuyātaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Suppose a person was walking through a forest. They’d see an ancient path, "
"an ancient route traveled by humans in the past."

msgctxt "sn12.65:7.2"
msgid "So tamanugaccheyya."
msgstr "Following it along,"

#. VAR: ajjhāvuṭṭhaṃ → ajjhāvutthaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1-2)
#. VAR: uddhāpavantaṃ → uddāpaṃ (bj) | uddāpavantaṃ (si, s1-3, km, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn12.65:7.3"
msgid ""
"Tamanugacchanto passeyya purāṇaṃ nagaraṃ purāṇaṃ rājadhāniṃ pubbakehi "
"manussehi ajjhāvuṭṭhaṃ ārāmasampannaṃ vanasampannaṃ pokkharaṇīsampannaṃ "
"uddhāpavantaṃ ramaṇīyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"they’d see an ancient city, an ancient capital, inhabited by humans in the "
"past. It was lovely, complete with parks, groves, lotus ponds, and "
"embankments."

msgctxt "sn12.65:7.4"
msgid "Atha kho so, bhikkhave, puriso rañño vā rājamahāmattassa vā āroceyya:"
msgstr "Then that person would inform a king or their minister:"

msgctxt "sn12.65:7.5"
msgid ""
"‘yagghe, bhante, jāneyyāsi—ahaṃ addasaṃ araññe pavane caramāno purāṇaṃ "
"maggaṃ purāṇañjasaṃ pubbakehi manussehi anuyātaṃ tamanugacchiṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘Please sir, you should know this. While walking through a forest I saw an "
"ancient path, an ancient route traveled by humans in the past."

msgctxt "sn12.65:7.6"
msgid ""
"Tamanugacchanto addasaṃ purāṇaṃ nagaraṃ purāṇaṃ rājadhāniṃ pubbakehi "
"manussehi ajjhāvuṭṭhaṃ ārāmasampannaṃ vanasampannaṃ pokkharaṇīsampannaṃ "
"uddhāpavantaṃ ramaṇīyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Following it along I saw an ancient city, an ancient capital, inhabited by "
"humans in the past. It was lovely, complete with parks, groves, lotus ponds, "
"and embankments."

msgctxt "sn12.65:7.7"
msgid "Taṃ, bhante, nagaraṃ māpehī’ti."
msgstr "Sir, you should rebuild that city!’"

msgctxt "sn12.65:7.8"
msgid "Atha kho so, bhikkhave, rājā vā rājamahāmatto vā taṃ nagaraṃ māpeyya."
msgstr "Then that king or their minister would have that city rebuilt."

msgctxt "sn12.65:7.9"
msgid ""
"Tadassa nagaraṃ aparena samayena iddhañceva phītañca bāhujaññaṃ "
"ākiṇṇamanussaṃ vuddhivepullappattaṃ."
msgstr ""
"And after some time that city was successful and prosperous and full of "
"people, attained to growth and expansion."

msgctxt "sn12.65:7.10"
msgid ""
"Evameva khvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, addasaṃ purāṇaṃ maggaṃ purāṇañjasaṃ pubbakehi "
"sammāsambuddhehi anuyātaṃ."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, I saw an ancient path, an ancient route traveled by fully "
"awakened Buddhas in the past."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.107"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.65:8.1"
msgid ""
"Katamo ca so, bhikkhave, purāṇamaggo purāṇañjaso pubbakehi sammāsambuddhehi "
"anuyāto?"
msgstr ""
"And what is that ancient path, the ancient road traveled by fully awakened "
"Buddhas in the past?"

msgctxt "sn12.65:8.2"
msgid "Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "It is simply this noble eightfold path, that is:"

msgctxt "sn12.65:8.3"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi."
msgstr ""
"right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, "
"right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion."

msgctxt "sn12.65:8.4"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ kho so, bhikkhave, purāṇamaggo purāṇañjaso pubbakehi sammāsambuddhehi "
"anuyāto, tamanugacchiṃ;"
msgstr ""
"This is that ancient path, the ancient road traveled by fully awakened "
"Buddhas in the past."

msgctxt "sn12.65:8.5"
msgid "tamanugacchanto jarāmaraṇaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ;"
msgstr "Following it along, I directly knew old age and death,"

msgctxt "sn12.65:8.6"
msgid "jarāmaraṇasamudayaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ;"
msgstr "their origin,"

msgctxt "sn12.65:8.7"
msgid "jarāmaraṇanirodhaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ;"
msgstr "their cessation,"

msgctxt "sn12.65:8.8"
msgid "jarāmaraṇanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ."
msgstr "and the practice that leads to their cessation."

msgctxt "sn12.65:8.9"
msgid "Tamanugacchiṃ;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.65:8.10"
msgid "tamanugacchanto jātiṃ abbhaññāsiṃ … pe …"
msgstr "Following it along, I directly knew rebirth …"

msgctxt "sn12.65:8.11"
msgid "bhavaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ …"
msgstr "continued existence …"

msgctxt "sn12.65:8.12"
msgid "upādānaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ …"
msgstr "grasping …"

msgctxt "sn12.65:8.13"
msgid "taṇhaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ …"
msgstr "craving …"

msgctxt "sn12.65:8.14"
msgid "vedanaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ …"
msgstr "feeling …"

msgctxt "sn12.65:8.15"
msgid "phassaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ …"
msgstr "contact …"

msgctxt "sn12.65:8.16"
msgid "saḷāyatanaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ …"
msgstr "the six sense fields …"

msgctxt "sn12.65:8.17"
msgid "nāmarūpaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ …"
msgstr "name and form …"

msgctxt "sn12.65:8.18"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ."
msgstr "consciousness …"

msgctxt "sn12.65:8.19"
msgid "Tamanugacchiṃ;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.65:8.20"
msgid "tamanugacchanto saṅkhāre abbhaññāsiṃ;"
msgstr "Following it along, I directly knew choices,"

msgctxt "sn12.65:8.21"
msgid "saṅkhārasamudayaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ;"
msgstr "their origin,"

msgctxt "sn12.65:8.22"
msgid "saṅkhāranirodhaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ;"
msgstr "their cessation,"

msgctxt "sn12.65:8.23"
msgid "saṅkhāranirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ."
msgstr "and the practice that leads to their cessation."

msgctxt "sn12.65:8.24"
msgid "Tadabhiññāya ācikkhiṃ bhikkhūnaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ upāsakānaṃ upāsikānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Having directly known this, I told the monks, nuns, laymen, and laywomen."

msgctxt "sn12.65:8.25"
msgid ""
"Tayidaṃ, bhikkhave, brahmacariyaṃ iddhañceva phītañca vitthārikaṃ bāhujaññaṃ "
"puthubhūtaṃ yāva devamanussehi suppakāsitan”ti."
msgstr ""
"And that’s how this spiritual life has become successful and prosperous, "
"extensive, popular, widespread, and well proclaimed wherever there are gods "
"and humans.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn12.65:8.26"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
